article.headline: Drake 36, William Penn 0
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Drake quarterback Ben Osterman tossed two touchdown passes and Logan Rees kicked three field goals to lead Drake to a 36-0 win over William Penn on Saturday. Osterman completed 16 of 30 passes for 201 yards. He threw touchdown strikes of 8 yards to Zach Brower and 42 yards to Stephen Platek for the Bulldogs (2-1). Logan kicked field goals of 22, 22 and 27 yards. Drake, which also got a 7-yard blocked punt return for a touchdown by Dain Taylor, outgained William Penn (1-2) 361-222 in total yards. Patrick Oliver led the Bulldogs in rushing with 92 yards. Michael Lahart scored on a 9-yard touchdown run in the third quarter. The Statesmen passed for just 63 yards. Quarterback Ryan Van Dalen was 4-for-12 with an interception and led William Penn in rushing with 70 yards on 12 carries. The Statesmen lost two of six fumbles.
